# Gastrocopta ogasawarana

| genus = Gastrocopta
| species = ogasawarana
| authority = Pilsbry, 1916
| synonyms =
}}
Gastrocopta ogasawarana was a species of very small air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Gastrocoptidae, the whorl snails. This small snail was endemic to Japan; it is now extinct.
